HEADWORD: CRO
<hw>CRO</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Electronics)</fld> <def>acronym for
<er>cathode-ray oscilloscope</er>, an electronic device which provides
visual images of varying electrical quantities. See
<er>oscilloscope</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> oscilloscope, scope, cathode-ray
oscilloscope.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

